dotterel
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:2
Definition:<i>Charadrius bicinctus</i>; a small New Zealand and Australian bird of the plover family, with two bands of colour across its breast, found on shores and riverbeds; also called  double-banded dotterell, New Zealand dotterel, tuturiwhatu.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
